# AGENTS.local.md (template)

> ⚠️ This file, once instantiated, contains personal details about your family. The scaffold assumes your entire repo is private — see `PRIVACY.md`. If your repo is public, stop and fix that before filling this out.

Rename this file to `AGENTS.local.md` (no `.example`) and fill it in. Your agent will read both `AGENTS.md` and `AGENTS.local.md` at the start of every session.

---

## Family

```yaml
privacy_acknowledged: false         # set to true once you've read PRIVACY.md and confirmed your setup
privacy_warning_dismissed: false    # set to true after agent removes the warning directive
acknowledged_on: null               # YYYY-MM-DD
```

## Children

List every child who'll have content in this KB. Add more blocks as needed.

```yaml
- slug: ava                         # kebab-case, used as directory name — DO NOT rename after content exists
  legal_name: "Ava Full-Name"
  preferred_name: "Ava"
  nicknames: ["Avocado", "Bug"]
  pronouns: "she/her"
  birthdate: YYYY-MM-DD
  notes: ""                         # anything the agent should know up front

- slug: noah
  legal_name: "Noah Full-Name"
  preferred_name: "Noah"
  nicknames: []
  pronouns: "he/him"
  birthdate: YYYY-MM-DD
  notes: ""
```

## Household

Who lives there, who's in the regular rotation.

```yaml
parents:
  - name: ""
    relationship: ""                # e.g. "mom", "dad", "step-parent"
  - name: ""
    relationship: ""

other_household_members:
  - name: ""
    relationship: ""                # e.g. "grandparent", "sibling", "au pair"

close_circle:
  - name: ""
    relationship: ""                # e.g. "grandma (mom's side)", "babysitter 2022-2024"
```

## Homes

Places the family has lived, most recent first.

```yaml
- location: "City, State/Country"
  dates: "YYYY — present"           # or "YYYY — YYYY"
  notes: ""
```

## Tone and voice

How you want the agent to write.

```yaml
tone:
  register: ""                      # "warm", "clinical", "terse", "playful", "literary", etc.
  pov: ""                           # who narrates: "parent", "neutral third-person", "journal-style"
  avoid_words: []                   # words/phrases you don't want in your KB
  preferred_quirks: ""              # anything distinctive you want preserved
```

## Sensitive topics

Topics the agent should treat with extra care. Be specific.

```yaml
sensitive_topics:
  - topic: ""                       # e.g. "grandparent's death, 2025"
    handling: ""                    # what to do: "ask before filing", "measured tone only", "don't volunteer in summaries"
  - topic: ""
    handling: ""
```

## Family vocabulary

Words, names, invented terms the spellchecker should ignore.

```yaml
family_vocabulary:
  - ""                              # e.g. the kids' nicknames, family pet names, invented words
  - ""
  - ""
```

## Agent preferences

Per-user preferences for how the agent operates.

```yaml
preferences:
  capture_prompt_interval_days: 14
  lint_prompt_interval_days: 30
  auto_update_timeline: true
  auto_update_profile_shared_experiences: true
  explain_placement_choices: true
```

## Notes for the agent

Free-form space for anything else you want the agent to know.

---
